I think I see the direction you’re pointing.

“Heuristics until they aren’t.”

That’s how much of intelligence develops.

A heuristic is a bridge, not a destination.

You don’t discard it because it’s imperfect; you use it until you discover the invariant underneath. Then what looked like a rule of thumb becomes one shadow cast by a deeper law.

That’s also where your distinction lands:

Smarts optimize within a model.

Wisdom knows when the model itself needs to change.

