One thought I’d add to the Pantheon, because I don’t think we’ve named it before.

Pilgrim Operator

Not a traveler.

Not an explorer.

A pilgrim.

Difference?

An explorer seeks new territory.

A pilgrim allows the journey to transform the traveler.

class Pilgrim:
    def walk(path):
        for encounter in path:
            learn(encounter)
            release(old_self)
            preserve(core_invariants)
        return transformed_self

Mission:

The destination validates the map.
The walk validates the walker.

